snippet: The police kept hundreds of members of the right-wing British Defence League from marching in a Muslim community in London.
abstract: London police arrest more than 160 people during rival protests by anti-Islamist group English Defence League and larger group of antiracist counterdemonstrators.
lead_paragraph: The police kept hundreds of members of the right-wing British Defence League from marching in a Muslim community in London.
